Philippa Bevans https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Philippa_Bevans 0 Philippa Bevans (10 Feb 1913 – 10 May 1968) was an English actress of stage and screen. She was born in London, England, and was the daughter of Ernest Bevans and Viola Roache . She was part of the cast of the original 1956 Broadway production of My Fair Lady that starred Rex Harrison and Julie Andrews and was featured on the original cast recording.
